Currently, the genus is composed by 22 species, 11 of which are from Africa, seven are from Colombia , three are from Brazil , and one is from the Democratic Republic of São Tomé and Príncipe (
;
,
, 2018;
;
). Hence, the current manuscript contributes significantly to the knowledge of this genus, especially in Brazil , as nine new species are described, bringing the total number of species known in the country to 12 and the total number of species in the genus to 31.
